    Complementary Results

    About

    Description

    Rembrandt Harmenszoon van Rijn, usually simply known as Rembrandt, was a Dutch Golden Age painter, printmaker, and draughtsman. An innovative and prolific master in three media, he is generally considered one of the greatest visual artists in the history of art. Wikipedia
    Born: July 15, 1606, Leiden, Netherlands
    Died: October 4, 1669, Amsterdam, Netherlands
    Periods: Baroque, Baroque painting, Dutch Golden Age
    Influenced by: Caravaggio, Titian, Hercules Seghers, Hendrick ter Brugghen
    Children: Cornelia van Rijn, Rumbartus van Rijn, Titus van Rijn
    Spouse: Saskia van Uylenburgh (m. 1634–1642)
